The paper deals with the classification of tilings of the Hamming cube, which is a problem in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The authors use linear maps and permutations, which are concepts from information theory (cs.IT) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also involves the explicit representation of permutations in cycles, which is a topic in combinatorics (cs.DS) and complexity theory (cs.CC).
